    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>National Briefing | Washington: 3 States Plan To Sue E.P.A.</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Andrew C. Revkin (NYT)</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Revkin, Andrew C</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Attorneys general of Connecticut, Massachusetts and Maine will sue EPA to force agency to restrict carbon dioxide as 'criteria pollutant' under terms of Clean Air Act (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The attorneys general of Connecticut, Massachusetts and Maine said they would sue the Environmental Protection Agency to force it to restrict carbon dioxide using the Clean Air Act. The officials, all Democrats, said the heat-trapping gas should be added to the ''criteria pollutants'' regulated under the act because data show that rising concentrations of carbon dioxide threaten ecosystems, agriculture and human health. Industry and conservative groups have said no restrictions are justified because no clear harm has been shown and because curbs would hurt the economy.</p>
        <p>Andrew C. Revkin (NYT)</p>
      </block>
